1.1 Introduction

Cryptography has existed for more than 4000 years, used by Egyptians[1]. It was used as a tool to protect national secrets and strategies.

In the modern day, the demand of cryptography started during 1960s when the
private sector needed a way to protect their information digitally. 

In 1977, D.E.S ( Data Encryption Standard ) was adopted for encrypting unclassified data. 
    - Most well known cryptographic mechanism in histroy.
    - Key length : 56 bits ( Too insecure for modern world )


